{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645311","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645311"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18103"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18103"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.73,0.08,0,0.11,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10817"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73532"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10817"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59001"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7385"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25178"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25181"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73532","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73532"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is superficial to the rotator cuff muscles?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Deltoid","Teres major","Subscapularis","Rhomboid major","Biceps brachii"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeltoid\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is superficial to the rotator cuff muscles, which include the supraspinatus, infraspinatus, teres minor, and subscapularis. The deltoid covers the shoulder joint and the rotator cuff muscles, providing the rounded contour of the shoulder.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBiceps brachii\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located in the anterior compartment of the arm and does not cover the rotator cuff\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETeres major\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located inferior to the rotator cuff muscles\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubscapularis\u003C/strong\u003E - This is one of the rotator cuff muscles itself\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERhomboid major\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located in the upper back and does not cover the rotator cuff\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The rotator cuff muscles are a group of four muscles that stabilize the shoulder joint.","The deltoid muscle is superficial to the rotator cuff muscles.","The rotator cuff muscles include supraspinatus, infraspinatus, teres minor, and subscapularis."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculos